	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Police have launched a manhunt following an attack on a cash-in-transit vehicle along Petroleum Road in Silverton, Pretoria, on Tuesday evening. Police spokesperson Captain Daniel Mavimbela said that a group of about 14 suspects were being sought, after they attacked the cash-in-transit vehicle. The suspects, driving in at least three vehicles - a Mercedes-Benz, Toyota Fortuna and a BMW - fired shots and forced the cash-in-transit vehicle off the road, before using explosives on the vehicle, said Mavimbela. The driver was assaulted during the attack and was being treated at a local hospital. "Investigations are expected to reveal whether there was any cash stolen during the attack," said Mavimbela.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  